<tr><td valign=top width=100% height=100% style='background: url(intr/background2.png) #f2f2f2; padding-top: 30px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 10px; padding-bottom: 30px;'>
<table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr height=20><td><nobr><a href='articles/thexeroxstararetrospective'><img width=9 height=20 style='margin-left: 16px' border=0 alt='Go back' src='intr/2captions/goback.png'></a></td><td valign=top height=20><img width=19 height=20 align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3toprise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 rowspan=3 width=100% style='background: url(intr/3topfill.png) white top repeat-x'><img border=0 alt='Further reading' style='margin-left: 3px; margin-top: 12px; margin-right: 10px' src='intr/3captions/furtherreading.png'></td><td valign=top style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)' height=20><img width=12 height=20 align=right hspace=0 src='intr/3topright.png'></td></tr><tr><td valign=top width=20 style='background: url(intr/3topleftfill.png) top repeat-x'><img width=20 height=20 hspace=0 src='intr/3topleft.png'></td><td valign=top><img align=left hspace=0 src='intr/3topleftrise.png'></td><td valign=top height=20 style='background: url(intr/3rightfill.png)'></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td width=20 height=50 style='background: url(intr/3leftfill.png) white left repeat-y;'><img width=20 height=1 src='intr/3leftfill.png'></td><td width=100% class=box3text style='background: white; padding-top: 20px; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 15px; '>
<p class=source>
A sidebar to the article <a href='articles/thexeroxstararetrospective'>&ldquo;The 
Xerox Star: A retrospective,&rdquo;</a> published in IEEE Computer, September 1989, pp. 27-28.
</p>

<table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td width=50% height=8 style='background: url(intr/divleftfill.png)'><img width=1 height=8 src='intr/divleftfill.png'></td><td width=8 height=8><img width=8 height=8 src='intr/divmed.png'></td><td width=50% height=8 style='background: url(intr/divrightfill.png)'><img width=1 height=8 src='intr/divrightfill.png'></td></tr></table>
<p>
For interested readers, we provide here a guide to further reading on Star 
and related topics. A more comprehensive and detailed version of this retrospective 
will appear in an upcoming Prentice-Hall book series. Also, the September 
issue of IEEE Spectrum includes an article, <a href='articles/ofmiceandmenus'>Of Mice and Menus</a>, on 
graphical user interfaces past and present. The authors of that article 
consulted several people who contributed to or are mentioned in this 
Star retrospective.
</p><p>
In the following bibliography, readings are categorized according to whether 
they pertain to work done prior to the establishment of Xerox PARC, to 
work done at PARC, to the original Star design done at Xerox 
SDD,<sup><small>8</small></sup> to enhancements to Star and ViewPoint, 
and to work on related topics.
</p><p class=caption>
Pre-Xerox
</p><p>
Bush, V., &ldquo;As We May Think,&rdquo; <i>Atlantic Monthly,</i> Vol. 176, No. 
1, July 1945, pp. 101-108.
</p><p>
Engelbart, D.C. and W.K. English, "A Research Center for Augmenting Human Intelect,"
<i>Proc. FJCC,</i> Vol. 33, AFIPS, 1968, pp. 395-410.
</p><p>
English, W.K., D.C. Engelbart, and M.L. Berman, "Display-Selection Techniques for
Text Manipulation," <i>IEEE Trans. Human Factors in Electronic,</i> HFE-8, 1967, pp. 
21-31.
</p><p>
Kay, A.C. <i>The Reactive Engine,</i> PhD thesis, University of Utah, Salt Lake City,
1969.
</p><p>
Sutherland, I.E., <i>Sketchpad: A Man-Machine Graphical Communications System,</i> PhD
thesis, M.I.T., Cambridge, Mass., 1963.
</p><p class=caption>
Xerox pre-Star
</p><p>
Card, S., W.K. English, and B. Burr, &ldquo;Evaluation of Mouse, Rate-Controlled Isometric 
Joystick, Step Keys, and Text Keys for Text Selection on a CRT,&rdquo; <i>Ergonomics,</i> 
Vol. 21, 1978, pp. 601-613.
</p><p>
Ellis, C, and G. Nutt, &ldquo;Computer Science and Office Information 
Systems,&rdquo; Xerox PARC Tech. Report SSL-79-6, 1979. 
</p><p>
Geschke, C.M., J.H. Morris, Jr., and E.H. Satter-thwaite, &ldquo;Early Experience 
with Mesa,&rdquo; <i>Comm. ACM,</i> Vol. 20, No. 8, 1977, pp. 540-553. 
</p><p>
Ingalls, D.H., &ldquo;The Smalltalk Graphics Kernel,&rdquo; <i>Byte,</i> Vol. 6, 
No. 8, Aug. 1981, pp. 168-194.
</p><p>
Kay, A.C., and A. Goldberg, &ldquo;Personal Dynamic Media,&rdquo; <i>Computer,</i> 
Vol. 10, No. 3, March 1977, pp. 31-41.
</p><p>
Kay, A.C., <a href='articles/microelectronicsandthepersonalcomputer'>Microelectronics and the Personal Computer</a>, <i>Scientific 
American,</i> Vol. 237, No. 3, Sept. 1977, pp. 230-244. 
</p><p>
Smith, D.C, <i>Pygmalion: A Computer Program to Model and Simulate Creative 
Thought,</i> Birkhauser Verlag, Basel and Stuttgart, 1977. 
</p><p>
Thacker, C.P., et al., &ldquo;Alto: A Personal Computer,&rdquo; in <i>Computer 
Structures: Principles and Examples,</i> D. Siewioek, C.G. Bell, and A. Newell, 
eds., McGraw Hill, New York, 1982.
</p><p class=caption>
Star
</p><p>
Curry, G., et al., &ldquo;Traits &ndash; An Approach to Multiple-Inheritance 
Subclassing,&rdquo; <i>Proc. ACM Conf. on Office Automation Systems (SIGOA),</i> 1982.
</p><p>
Dalai, Y.K., &ldquo;Use of Multiple Networks in the Xerox Network 
System,&rdquo; <i>Computer,</i> Vol. 15, No. 10, Oct. 1982, pp. 82-92. 
</p><p>
Johnsson, R.K., and J.D. Wick, &ldquo;An Overview of the Mesa Processor 
Architecture,&rdquo; <i>SIGPlan Notices,</i> Vol. 17, No. 4, 1982. 
</p><p>
Lipkie, D.E., et al., &ldquo;Star Graphics: An Object-Oriented Implementation,&rdquo; 
<i>Computer Graphics,</i> Vol. 16, No. 3, July 1982, pp. 115-124. 
</p><p>
Shoch, J.F., et al., &ldquo;Evolution of the Ethernet Local Computer 
Network,&rdquo; <i>Computer,</i> Vol. 15, No. 9, Aug. 1982, pp. 10-27. 
</p><p>
Smith, D.C, et al., <a href='articles/designingthestaruserinterface'>Designing the Star User Interface</a>, <i>Byte,</i> 
Vol. 7, No. 4, April 1982, pp. 242-282.
</p><p>
Sweet, R.E., and J.G. Sandman, Jr., &ldquo;Empirical Analysis of the Mesa 
Instruction Set,&rdquo; <i>SIGPlan Notices,</i> Vol. 17, No. 4, 1982.
</p><p class=caption>
Star/ViewPoint enhancements
</p><p>
Becker, J., &ldquo;Typing Chinese, Japanese, and Korean,&rdquo; <i>Computer,</i> Vol. 
18, No. 1, Jan. 1985, pp. 27-34.
</p><p>
Becker, J., &ldquo;Arabic Word Processing,&rdquo; <i>Comm. ACM,</i> Vol. 30, 
No. 7, July 1987, pp. 600-610. 
</p><p>
Bewley, W.L., et al., <a href='articles/humanfactorstestinginthedesignofxeroxs8010starofficeworkstation'>Human Factors Testing in the Design of 
Xerox&rsquo;s 8010 Star Office Workstation</a>, <i>Proc. ACM Conf. on Human 
Factors in Computing Systems,</i> 1983, pp. 72-77.
</p><p>
Bushan, A., and M. Plass, &ldquo;The Interpress Page and Document Description 
Language,&rdquo; <i>Computer,</i> Vol. 19, No. 6, June 1986, pp. 72-77. 
</p><p>
Curry, G., and R. Ayers, &ldquo;Experience with Traits in Star,&rdquo; 
<i>Programming Productivity: Issues for the Eighties,</i> IEEE Computer Society 
Press, Los Alamitos, Calif., 1986, Order #681. 
</p><p>
Halbert, D., &ldquo;Programming by Example,&rdquo; Xerox OSD Tech. Report 
OSD-T84-02, 1984. 
</p><p>
Lewis, B., and J. Hodges, &ldquo;Shared Books: Collaborative Publication 
Management for an Office Information System,&rdquo; <i>Proc. ACM Conf. 
on Office Information Systems,</i> 1988.
</p><p class=caption>
Miscellaneous
</p><p>
Bly, S., and J. Rosenberg, &ldquo;A Comparison of Tiled and Overlapping 
Windows,&rdquo; <i>Proc. ACM Conf. on Computer-Human Interaction,</i> 1986, pp. 101-106.
</p><p>
Goldberg, A., <i>Smalltalk-80: The Interactive Programming Environment,</i> 
Addison-Wesley Publishing, Reading, Mass., 1984. 
</p><p>
Goldberg, A., and D. Robson, <i>Smalltalk-80: The Language and its 
Implementation,</i> Addison-Wesley Publishing, Reading, Mass., 1984.
</p><p>
Halasz, F., and T. Moran, &ldquo;Analogy Considered Harmful,&rdquo; <i>Proc. ACM 
Conf. on Human Factors in Computing Systems,</i> Gaithersburg, MD, 1982, pp. 383-386. 
</p><p>
Houston, T., &ldquo;The Allegory of Software: Beyond, Behind, and Beneath 
the Electronic Desk,&rdquo; <i>Byte,</i> Dec. 1983, pp. 210-214. 
</p><p>
Johnson, J., &ldquo;Calculator Functions on Bitmapped Computers,&rdquo; <i>SIGCHI 
Bulletin,</i> Vol. 17, No. 1, July 1985, pp. 23-28. 
</p><p>
Johnson, J., &ldquo;How Closely Should the Electronic Desktop Simulate the 
Real One?&rdquo; <i>SIGCHI Bulletin,</i> Vol. 19, No. 2, Oct. 1987, pp. 21-25.
</p><p>
Johnson, J., &ldquo;Modes in Non-Computer Devices,&rdquo; in press, 
<i>Int&rsquo;l J. Man-Machine Studies,</i> 1989.
</p><p>
Johnson, J., and R. Beach, &ldquo;Styles in Document Editing 
Systems,&rdquo; <i>Computer,</i> Vol. 21, No. 1, Jan. 1988, pp. 32-43.
</p><p>
Malone, T.W., &ldquo;How Do People Organize Their Desks: Implications for the 
Design of Office Information Systems,&rdquo; <i>ACM Trans. on Office Information 
Systems,</i> Vol. 1, No. 1, 1983, pp. 99-112.
</p><p>
Rosenberg, J.K., and T.P. Moran, &ldquo;Generic Commands,&rdquo; <i>Proc. 
First Int&rsquo;l Conf. on Human-Computer Interaction (Interact-84),</i> 
1984, pp. 1,360-1,364.
</p><p>
Teitelman, W., &ldquo;A Tour Through Cedar,&rdquo; <i>IEEE Software,</i> April 1984.
</p><p>
Whiteside, J., et al., &ldquo;User Performance with Command, Menu, and 
Iconic Interfaces,&rdquo; <i>Proc. ACM SIGCHI &rsquo;85,</i> 1985, pp. 185-191.
</p>

